00:57:56.700 --> 00:57:57.700
I don't know.

00:57:57.700 --> 00:57:59.700
He came here.

00:57:59.700 --> 00:58:02.700
I don't remember.

00:58:02.700 --> 00:58:07.700
He would come to Palmers, down his seat and say, John.

00:58:07.700 --> 00:58:14.700
I don't know if he would go to the church, but in the 50s he would come through trying to organize.

00:58:14.700 --> 00:58:20.700
I don't know if he would mass media dreams.

00:58:20.700 --> 00:58:22.700
So what I did?

00:58:22.700 --> 00:58:28.700
I thought you'd come into that mass media.

00:58:28.700 --> 00:58:36.700
She was there just as proud that she could be in a starch and iron dress.

00:58:36.700 --> 00:58:43.700
She was calling her the nervous and nervous.

00:58:43.700 --> 00:58:48.700
She'd tell her, no.

00:58:48.700 --> 00:58:52.700
I'm not going to.

00:58:52.700 --> 00:58:57.700
She could sit there, nervous and nervous.

00:58:57.700 --> 00:58:58.700
Did you?

00:58:58.700 --> 00:59:00.700
What did she think that night?

00:59:00.700 --> 00:59:05.700
Go tell it on the mountain.

00:59:05.700 --> 00:59:10.700
So this was the day in 63 then because it was the 4th freedom day?

00:59:10.700 --> 00:59:12.700
Yes.

00:59:12.700 --> 00:59:16.700
It was 4th freedom day.

00:59:16.700 --> 00:59:23.700
This must have been like after they had gone to Washington.

00:59:23.700 --> 00:59:26.700
Oh, after the March on Washington.

00:59:26.700 --> 00:59:29.700
This was after that.

00:59:29.700 --> 00:59:43.700
It must have been like September because I'm thinking it was full Christmas that I went to the church.

00:59:43.700 --> 00:59:50.700
So you were pretty quickly went to Dorchester Center and you were teaching the citizenship class.

00:59:50.700 --> 00:59:53.700
Do you remember Jean Wheeler?

00:59:53.700 --> 00:59:55.700
Jean Wheeler?

00:59:55.700 --> 00:59:57.700
She stayed at the school.

00:59:57.700 --> 01:00:00.700
Yes, I know Jean.

01:00:00.700 --> 01:00:02.700
Tell me what she was like.

01:00:02.700 --> 01:00:06.700
With a little shout skirt.

01:00:06.700 --> 01:00:11.700
Oh boy, she could wear those shorts.

01:00:11.700 --> 01:00:15.700
Yes, I remember her.

01:00:15.700 --> 01:00:18.700
You remember she organized in the MFEP?

01:00:18.700 --> 01:00:21.700
Yes.

01:00:21.700 --> 01:00:25.700
And then she soon moved away.

01:00:25.700 --> 01:00:32.700
I don't know everywhere she went but I know in the summer of 64 she was in Philadelphia.

01:00:32.700 --> 01:00:35.700
That's probably what she was.

01:00:35.700 --> 01:00:46.700
She said she wanted to make sure that the clan knew they weren't going to win in Philadelphia.

01:00:46.700 --> 01:00:48.700
Was she a good organizer?

01:00:48.700 --> 01:00:55.700
Yes, she was.

01:00:55.700 --> 01:01:00.700
So how did you manage to keep up your beauty shop and your children?

01:01:00.700 --> 01:01:05.700
I wanted that too and my daughter talked about it.

01:01:05.700 --> 01:01:09.700
She said I never miss nothing when I went to school.

01:01:09.700 --> 01:01:12.700
She said that?

01:01:12.700 --> 01:01:17.700
I'd be in the shop and I would leave people in the shop.

01:01:17.700 --> 01:01:23.700
They'd wait till I go to her programs and whatever and they'd be waiting until I come back.

01:01:23.700 --> 01:01:27.700
She said she's...

01:01:27.700 --> 01:01:31.700
Somebody would tell her, you know my man coming, she's working.

01:01:31.700 --> 01:01:33.700
My mama will be here.

01:01:33.700 --> 01:01:36.700
So she's standing in the street looking up.

01:01:36.700 --> 01:01:40.700
So she said, here she come now.

01:01:40.700 --> 01:01:43.700
I wanted to...

01:01:43.700 --> 01:01:45.700
I don't know.

01:01:45.700 --> 01:01:47.700
I did all I did.

01:01:47.700 --> 01:01:50.700
Did you have health in the shop?

01:01:50.700 --> 01:01:53.700
I worked by myself.

01:01:53.700 --> 01:01:56.700
I didn't have...

01:01:56.700 --> 01:02:00.700
I was all lonely beauty operator.

01:02:00.700 --> 01:02:06.700
And I was having problems with the other beauticians and all, you know.

01:02:06.700 --> 01:02:07.700
What kind of problems?

01:02:07.700 --> 01:02:21.700
They would tell some of my clan tales that you go full-riding and you're going to get burned up in that shop with her.

01:02:21.700 --> 01:02:27.700
They kill my business because they ain't mind waiting on me.

01:02:27.700 --> 01:02:34.700
That's when I went to work at the hand back.

01:02:34.700 --> 01:02:37.700
Because you lost so many customers?

01:02:37.700 --> 01:02:42.700
I would still catch some when I come get off and work and all.

01:02:42.700 --> 01:02:45.700
Were they afraid because of the movement?

01:02:45.700 --> 01:02:48.700
Were they afraid that they were going to...

01:02:48.700 --> 01:02:51.700
They must have been.

01:02:51.700 --> 01:02:54.700
They did health.

01:02:54.700 --> 01:02:57.700
Did your business come back after?

01:02:57.700 --> 01:03:00.700
I wasn't going back.

01:03:00.700 --> 01:03:03.700
I...

01:03:06.700 --> 01:03:09.700
I lost my top.

01:03:09.700 --> 01:03:12.700
Were you talking about your customers?

01:03:12.700 --> 01:03:15.700
Yeah.

01:03:15.700 --> 01:03:18.700
And one customer...

01:03:18.700 --> 01:03:27.700
Her boss, her husband, was a clansman.

01:03:27.700 --> 01:03:33.700
And she would tell me things, you know, about being...

01:03:33.700 --> 01:03:36.700
When they were going up there to...

01:03:36.700 --> 01:03:40.700
to fight up there at Oxford.

01:03:40.700 --> 01:03:43.700
So when Meredith...

01:03:43.700 --> 01:03:46.700
You say if I'd up at Oxford, was that when James Meredith was there?

01:03:46.700 --> 01:03:48.700
Yes, right.

01:03:48.700 --> 01:03:50.700
So she knew about the clan going up there?

01:03:50.700 --> 01:03:52.700
Oh, yeah.

01:03:52.700 --> 01:03:54.700
She knew all about...

01:03:54.700 --> 01:03:55.700
They don't pay...

01:03:55.700 --> 01:03:59.700
You know, they would talk in front of you...

01:03:59.700 --> 01:04:02.700
as if you weren't there.

01:04:02.700 --> 01:04:06.700
They didn't think you had since enough to tell me about it or nothing.

01:04:06.700 --> 01:04:13.700
Because that's what I was telling one of the women that would go up there to the precincts.

01:04:13.700 --> 01:04:16.700
Because we worked the precinct.

01:04:16.700 --> 01:04:19.700
Because the...

01:04:19.700 --> 01:04:25.700
Corporal workers would give us a thing saying that we were supposed to be there.

01:04:25.700 --> 01:04:27.700
For what?

01:04:27.700 --> 01:04:29.700
Yeah.

01:04:29.700 --> 01:04:32.700
And they would just be talking and a lot of stuff.

01:04:32.700 --> 01:04:34.700
They would just talk about it.

01:04:34.700 --> 01:04:37.700
And one lady said, they don't...

01:04:37.700 --> 01:04:41.700
They were talking all in front of us.

01:04:41.700 --> 01:04:45.700
I said, honey, they don't count us.

01:04:45.700 --> 01:04:54.700
They all they got to do is say, I didn't say it and you go, you don't catch it for the time.

01:04:54.700 --> 01:04:59.700
Did that change when people were able to vote?

01:04:59.700 --> 01:05:01.700
Did that attitude...

01:05:01.700 --> 01:05:03.700
Did it change at all after voting?

01:05:03.700 --> 01:05:07.700
No.

01:05:07.700 --> 01:05:14.700
I worked a long time on the polls.

01:05:14.700 --> 01:05:17.700
Heap on count the votes.

01:05:17.700 --> 01:05:24.700
And...

01:05:24.700 --> 01:05:25.700
I never...

01:05:25.700 --> 01:05:27.700
Nobody never bothered me.

01:05:27.700 --> 01:05:29.700
Never.

01:05:29.700 --> 01:05:31.700
You would tell them you would...

01:05:31.700 --> 01:05:34.700
I want to say I worked for nothing.

01:05:34.700 --> 01:05:37.700
But they weren't getting the $3.

01:05:37.700 --> 01:05:39.700
But they weren't paying anything.

01:05:39.700 --> 01:05:41.700
Everyone's paying me nothing.

01:05:41.700 --> 01:05:43.700
Were they working for the Democratic Party?

01:05:43.700 --> 01:05:45.700
The Regulus?

01:05:45.700 --> 01:05:48.700
Or was that working for the election?

01:05:48.700 --> 01:05:50.700
For election.

01:05:50.700 --> 01:05:51.700
Commission?

01:05:51.700 --> 01:05:52.700
Yeah.

01:05:52.700 --> 01:05:56.700
You know, I've often wondered about this.

01:05:56.700 --> 01:06:00.700
They must have a election commission back then.

01:06:00.700 --> 01:06:06.700
Because the people they worked for were the ones that counted the votes.

01:06:06.700 --> 01:06:10.700
And certified and all that.

01:06:10.700 --> 01:06:15.700
I don't really remember anything about election commission

01:06:15.700 --> 01:06:24.700
to few years later and some Black Start campaign.

01:06:24.700 --> 01:06:26.700
I don't really know how it worked.

01:06:26.700 --> 01:06:29.700
But I know in Claiborne County there were white election commissioners

01:06:29.700 --> 01:06:31.700
until after the voting rights act.

01:06:31.700 --> 01:06:33.700
And then they got beat a couple of them.

01:06:33.700 --> 01:06:36.700
So then there was an integrated group.

01:06:36.700 --> 01:06:41.700
And then eventually I think half-CinAmerican one, four out of five.

01:06:41.700 --> 01:06:44.700
But they didn't have it before.

01:06:44.700 --> 01:06:46.700
But I'm not sure how it worked.

01:06:46.700 --> 01:06:48.700
I think it was just on the book.

01:06:48.700 --> 01:06:49.700
That could be.

01:06:49.700 --> 01:06:51.700
That makes sense.

01:06:51.700 --> 01:06:55.700
I don't really need it.

01:06:55.700 --> 01:06:58.700
You were telling me before about how you got arrested.

01:06:58.700 --> 01:07:01.700
And then you were going to get arrested?

01:07:01.700 --> 01:07:02.700
Oh, yes.

01:07:02.700 --> 01:07:07.700
We went up there.

01:07:07.700 --> 01:07:09.700
We made a round around.

01:07:09.700 --> 01:07:10.700
Not a round.

01:07:10.700 --> 01:07:17.700
You've won't go any into the round by the jail.

01:07:17.700 --> 01:07:23.700
Come up by the Masonic Temple and to the furniture store.

01:07:23.700 --> 01:07:27.700
And the line was going around.

01:07:27.700 --> 01:07:31.700
So in front of the courthouse kind of back and forth in front of the courthouse?

01:07:31.700 --> 01:07:32.700
No.

01:07:32.700 --> 01:07:34.700
We went all the way around.

01:07:34.700 --> 01:07:36.700
So almost all the way around the building?

01:07:36.700 --> 01:07:41.700
You couldn't, well no sidewalk next to the furniture store.

01:07:41.700 --> 01:07:45.700
That's stricken and furniture I think it was.

01:07:45.700 --> 01:07:47.700
So you had to turn.

01:07:47.700 --> 01:07:51.700
But it's a line going and a line coming.

01:07:51.700 --> 01:07:54.700
And then you got to get the inside of the computer.

01:07:54.700 --> 01:08:00.700
So is this before Freedom Day?

01:08:00.700 --> 01:08:01.700
Oh, no.

01:08:01.700 --> 01:08:02.700
No.

01:08:02.700 --> 01:08:04.700
I was after it.

01:08:04.700 --> 01:08:06.700
After Freedom Day.

01:08:06.700 --> 01:08:09.700
Okay.

01:08:09.700 --> 01:08:12.700
But that's when the menaces came down.

01:08:12.700 --> 01:08:16.700
And a lot of other workers and other states.

01:08:16.700 --> 01:08:18.700
And we had a lot of people.

01:08:18.700 --> 01:08:20.700
For Freedom Day?

01:08:20.700 --> 01:08:23.700
And the worker came the night before.

01:08:23.700 --> 01:08:24.700
Did you hear him?

01:08:24.700 --> 01:08:26.700
You were there?

01:08:26.700 --> 01:08:28.700
Right there.

01:08:28.700 --> 01:08:35.700
And you know when you go in the church you would think some people would have summer of spring.

01:08:35.700 --> 01:08:39.700
He'd have put his foot up on me.

01:08:39.700 --> 01:08:45.700
I've heard some of the things he used to say.

01:08:45.700 --> 01:08:48.700
He was terrible.

01:08:48.700 --> 01:08:50.700
He was okay.

01:08:50.700 --> 01:08:51.700
I like him.

01:08:51.700 --> 01:08:56.700
Did you tell him to say did you enjoy it when you were in?

01:08:56.700 --> 01:08:57.700
I like him.

01:08:57.700 --> 01:09:00.700
Did you hear him talking back to the officers?

01:09:00.700 --> 01:09:03.700
Oh yeah.

01:09:03.700 --> 01:09:04.700
What do you remember?

01:09:04.700 --> 01:09:07.700
What else do you remember about Freedom Day?

01:09:07.700 --> 01:09:09.700
Freedom Day.

01:09:09.700 --> 01:09:12.700
It was Poin Down Ring.

01:09:12.700 --> 01:09:17.700
And police didn't have no...

01:09:17.700 --> 01:09:20.700
Rain gear.

01:09:20.700 --> 01:09:27.700
One of the stores downtown gave them all rain coats.

01:09:27.700 --> 01:09:33.700
And that's how they stayed out there all day in that rain.

01:09:33.700 --> 01:09:35.700
But it was...

01:09:35.700 --> 01:09:40.700
You just felt like you was free, you know?

01:09:40.700 --> 01:09:46.700
And I was talking to one writer.

01:09:46.700 --> 01:09:51.700
He said, why were you out there?

01:09:51.700 --> 01:09:57.700
I was getting my freedom.

01:09:57.700 --> 01:10:04.700
And Jerry Nash.

01:10:04.700 --> 01:10:08.700
He thought that was the funnest thing.

01:10:08.700 --> 01:10:11.700
Getting my freedom.

01:10:11.700 --> 01:10:16.700
Did any of the people coming into town doing the ministers?

01:10:16.700 --> 01:10:19.700
Did they stay with you or any of you?

01:10:19.700 --> 01:10:20.700
Oh yeah.

01:10:20.700 --> 01:10:25.700
It's a lot of people came to Rep. John Conyers Jr.

01:10:25.700 --> 01:10:28.700
He stayed at my house.

01:10:28.700 --> 01:10:32.700
And I was told after was...

01:10:32.700 --> 01:10:36.700
FBI agents stayed.

01:10:36.700 --> 01:10:40.700
I guess they wanted to make sure nothing happened to the congressman.

01:10:40.700 --> 01:10:47.700
So it was fun.

01:10:47.700 --> 01:10:55.700
And I didn't have to be a street skater.

01:10:55.700 --> 01:10:58.700
And my dad would take shifts.

01:10:58.700 --> 01:11:02.700
You know, he'd stay up.

01:11:02.700 --> 01:11:09.700
My mother would go to bed early and he would get up and stay up at...

01:11:09.700 --> 01:11:15.700
He had been paralyzed, but he started walking and he had a cane.

01:11:15.700 --> 01:11:18.700
And the cane was the man across us.

01:11:18.700 --> 01:11:23.700
And people put out that old man sitting there with a shotgun across his leg.

01:11:23.700 --> 01:11:28.700
Probably got me a day, put that out.

01:11:28.700 --> 01:11:30.700
Yeah.

01:11:30.700 --> 01:11:32.700
That was the word.

01:11:32.700 --> 01:11:34.700
He was sitting there with a shotgun.

01:11:34.700 --> 01:11:38.700
Did you get threatened with people threatening you?

01:11:38.700 --> 01:11:41.700
Nobody threatened me.

01:11:41.700 --> 01:11:49.700
But after we come back from watching, from New Jersey,

01:11:49.700 --> 01:11:53.700
and you know who we went up there to?

01:11:53.700 --> 01:11:56.700
Atlantic City.

01:11:56.700 --> 01:12:05.700
And Los Angeles.

01:12:05.700 --> 01:12:08.700
And you asked if you were threatened.

01:12:08.700 --> 01:12:11.700
Oh, I was going to tell you.

01:12:11.700 --> 01:12:15.700
I'd never been on my airplane before my life.

01:12:15.700 --> 01:12:19.700
And we were campaigning for...

01:12:19.700 --> 01:12:24.700
Me and the main Johnson.

01:12:24.700 --> 01:12:27.700
And I went to New York.

01:12:27.700 --> 01:12:32.700
Johnny Cameron went to Philadelphia, I think it was.

01:12:32.700 --> 01:12:43.700
And just different, one of the delegates, we went to other states campaigning for him.

01:12:43.700 --> 01:12:49.700
My telephone bill, I had got a telephone about that time.

01:12:49.700 --> 01:12:58.700
But anyway, they knew I had got on the phone, somebody.

01:12:58.700 --> 01:13:04.700
I mean, they got on the plane and daddy asked us to phone.

01:13:04.700 --> 01:13:09.700
And they told us that our telephone bill is due.

01:13:09.700 --> 01:13:15.700
It didn't have to be paid back by the clock, or we couldn't get out.

01:13:15.700 --> 01:13:21.700
It's one of the things my daddy just wouldn't pay to be here.

01:13:21.700 --> 01:13:24.700
I don't think it was about $15.

01:13:24.700 --> 01:13:25.700
Yeah.

01:13:25.700 --> 01:13:28.700
And it wouldn't be the problem.

01:13:28.700 --> 01:13:31.700
That was they were going to get you with that?

01:13:31.700 --> 01:13:34.700
I guess, I don't know.

01:13:34.700 --> 01:13:37.700
So I couldn't call back.

01:13:37.700 --> 01:13:42.700
But I wasn't threatened.

01:13:42.700 --> 01:13:51.700
And my daughter, when Felicia [Connor], when they desegregated [the] self-created [white] schools",

01:13:51.700 --> 01:13:57.700
and she was six to integrate.

01:13:57.700 --> 01:14:00.700
Yeah. Freedom of choice.

01:14:00.700 --> 01:14:03.700
Did she want to do that?

01:14:03.700 --> 01:14:05.700
She didn't know.

01:14:05.700 --> 01:14:09.700
You know, back then, children did what you say to them.

01:14:09.700 --> 01:14:11.700
And they didn't question.

01:14:11.700 --> 01:14:18.700
And I said to myself, I had been out to California with my sister,

01:14:18.700 --> 01:14:23.700
and what happened about that time?

01:14:23.700 --> 01:14:27.700
So daddy told me I need to come home.

01:14:27.700 --> 01:14:34.700
And I got home like two days before the registration would end.

01:14:34.700 --> 01:14:41.700
And she was a little plump girl.

01:14:41.700 --> 01:14:44.700
And she was just skipping all the way.

01:14:44.700 --> 01:14:45.700
That's a lot of him.

01:14:45.700 --> 01:14:50.700
She was a baby, don't know what I'm getting into.

01:14:50.700 --> 01:14:53.700
And we went up to the old headless bird car.

01:14:53.700 --> 01:14:55.700
It's burning.

01:14:55.700 --> 01:14:57.700
It had a lot of...

01:14:57.700 --> 01:15:01.700
You haven't got it fixed yet.

01:15:01.700 --> 01:15:04.700
She went up there.

01:15:04.700 --> 01:15:10.700
And I didn't even know that the school name.

01:15:10.700 --> 01:15:14.700
I know it was on 7th Street, crossing Herkley.

01:15:14.700 --> 01:15:16.700
It was the name Jefferson Davis Elementary School.

01:15:16.700 --> 01:15:21.700
I did, but I had never paid no attention.

01:15:21.700 --> 01:15:24.700
And so he said, what school...

01:15:24.700 --> 01:15:28.700
What school you want to send that girl to?

01:15:28.700 --> 01:15:31.700
I said, I don't know the name of it.

01:15:31.700 --> 01:15:35.700
I said, but it's located across from Hercules."

01:15:35.700 --> 01:15:39.700
He said, Jefferson Davis.

01:15:39.700 --> 01:15:44.700
Are you ready to change my name?

01:15:44.700 --> 01:15:48.700
Absolutely, okay.

01:15:48.700 --> 01:15:49.700
She didn't know.

01:15:49.700 --> 01:15:52.700
She just know she was changing school.

01:15:52.700 --> 01:15:57.700
And she's talked to some of the white kids later.

01:15:57.700 --> 01:16:00.700
After they graduated from high school and all.

01:16:00.700 --> 01:16:04.700
They didn't know what was going on either.

01:16:04.700 --> 01:16:09.700
After I come these strange children coming to my room late.

01:16:09.700 --> 01:16:12.700
See, all the kids were in that classroom.

01:16:12.700 --> 01:16:15.700
And then they take the children to...

01:16:15.700 --> 01:16:18.700
They go to the black school first and then they carry them away?

01:16:18.700 --> 01:16:19.700
No, no, no, no.

01:16:19.700 --> 01:16:22.700
Parents had to bring them.

01:16:22.700 --> 01:16:28.700
But they would hold those kids until all the white kids get in that class and that seat.

01:16:28.700 --> 01:16:31.700
And then the teacher would walk on the end.

01:16:31.700 --> 01:16:36.700
And then they would say, is that why they would do that?

01:16:36.700 --> 01:16:38.700
I don't know.

01:16:38.700 --> 01:16:40.700
Make sure there wasn't any fighting.

01:16:40.700 --> 01:16:42.700
It wasn't nothing going on.

