02:15:14.700 --> 02:15:20.700
He was a national.

02:15:20.700 --> 02:15:23.700
So why did they put you on the third floor?

02:15:23.700 --> 02:15:26.700
I don't know.

02:15:26.700 --> 02:15:29.700
I was up there.

02:15:29.700 --> 02:15:36.700
They tried to make sure he didn't organize everybody else.

02:15:36.700 --> 02:15:39.700
I don't know.

02:15:39.700 --> 02:15:42.700
And Monica went to Monica.

02:15:42.700 --> 02:15:46.700
He got away with the jail thing too.

02:15:46.700 --> 02:15:53.700
We had to pay money to get out of it but we got it back.

02:15:53.700 --> 02:16:00.700
Some people, some of her people sent money to my daddy.

02:16:00.700 --> 02:16:05.700
And my daddy got both of us up the same day.

02:16:05.700 --> 02:16:08.700
So was she working in Harrisburg?

02:16:08.700 --> 02:16:12.700
She came here when she first came to the state.

02:16:12.700 --> 02:16:14.700
She worked in Hattiesburg,

02:16:14.700 --> 02:16:18.700
And then she moved to Jackson.

02:16:18.700 --> 02:16:22.700
So did she come in freedom somewhere?

02:16:22.700 --> 02:16:24.700
Yeah.

02:16:24.700 --> 02:16:26.700
And she stayed at my house.

02:16:26.700 --> 02:16:29.700
Oh, did she?

02:16:29.700 --> 02:16:32.700
I didn't know that.

02:16:32.700 --> 02:16:37.700
She said daddy was like a daddy to her.

02:16:37.700 --> 02:16:40.700
Yeah.

02:16:40.700 --> 02:16:43.700
And he was on the codes.

02:16:43.700 --> 02:16:46.700
And they ended up there.

02:16:46.700 --> 02:16:48.700
Washington.

02:16:48.700 --> 02:16:50.700
No, in Jackson?

02:16:50.700 --> 02:16:53.700
Oh, and then eventually Washington.

02:16:53.700 --> 02:16:56.700
So they were both working in Jackson.

02:16:56.700 --> 02:16:59.700
What was that protest about in Jackson?

02:16:59.700 --> 02:17:05.700
Or you got arrested?

02:17:05.700 --> 02:17:11.700
It was something about trying to date.

02:17:11.700 --> 02:17:14.700
We were.

02:17:14.700 --> 02:17:26.700
They were in session.

02:17:26.700 --> 02:17:32.700
And they just made you get their homes in session.

02:17:32.700 --> 02:17:40.700
And it's something that they were playing on, voting on,

02:17:40.700 --> 02:17:43.700
stop demonstrations in Jackson.

02:17:43.700 --> 02:17:48.700
And we went to the capital.

02:17:48.700 --> 02:17:54.700
We didn't get a chance to do no kind of ticket to him or nothing.

02:17:54.700 --> 02:17:57.700
We had our little things, you know.

02:17:57.700 --> 02:18:03.700
But out of the car, I got into Pateaway.

02:18:03.700 --> 02:18:06.700
That's right.

02:18:06.700 --> 02:18:11.700
Didn't you?

02:18:11.700 --> 02:18:12.700
So they did.

02:18:12.700 --> 02:18:17.700
Whatever it was, I don't think they ever passed it.

02:18:17.700 --> 02:18:26.700
It was a special session called for that.

02:18:26.700 --> 02:18:33.700
And I sing the thing and a lot of us sing the thing.

02:18:33.700 --> 02:18:36.700
Read nothing was done too much.

02:18:36.700 --> 02:18:40.700
He had his bird because the governor was from Hattiesburg. (Paul Burney) Johnson Jr.

02:18:40.700 --> 02:18:43.700
Call the Johnson.

02:18:43.700 --> 02:18:47.700
And I was in Hattiesburg.

02:18:47.700 --> 02:18:51.700
And so that kind of kept it down.

02:18:51.700 --> 02:18:55.700
Because most of the people here in Hattiesburg,

02:18:55.700 --> 02:19:02.700
they didn't want the news to get out.

02:19:02.700 --> 02:19:05.700
Something happened in Hattiesburg.

02:19:05.700 --> 02:19:08.700
So they tried to keep things under control?

02:19:08.700 --> 02:19:14.700
Yeah. And that's the same way when we integrated schools.

02:19:14.700 --> 02:19:17.700
They wouldn't go hand on demonstrations in front of the schools.

02:19:17.700 --> 02:19:24.700
You know, like parents and everybody else come out and nobody come to school with the children.

02:19:24.700 --> 02:19:29.700
So they tried to keep the white leadership, tried to keep the world's town,

02:19:29.700 --> 02:19:32.700
keep out of the news.

02:19:32.700 --> 02:19:35.700
And you think it's because it was Johnson's hometown?

02:19:35.700 --> 02:19:38.700
And he lived.

02:19:38.700 --> 02:19:42.700
Yeah, I don't believe that.

02:19:42.700 --> 02:19:46.700
So here we are at Southern,

02:19:46.700 --> 02:19:52.700
which was segregated until the 60s.

02:19:52.700 --> 02:19:55.700
Has it changed?

02:19:55.700 --> 02:20:00.700
Yes. We have, I was told,

02:20:00.700 --> 02:20:07.700
we have more black students on this campus than any other.

02:20:07.700 --> 02:20:13.700
I was told school in the state that include the blacks and the whites.

02:20:13.700 --> 02:20:15.700
It's a big school, isn't it?

02:20:15.700 --> 02:20:17.700
It's a big campus here.

02:20:17.700 --> 02:20:23.700
And it's got a lot of most of people up there.

02:20:23.700 --> 02:20:27.700
Is it? I knew it had changed a lot.

02:20:27.700 --> 02:20:31.700
So does that make you happy about that?

02:20:31.700 --> 02:20:35.700
Well, yes.

02:20:35.700 --> 02:20:38.700
I'm alright with it.

02:20:38.700 --> 02:20:46.700
It's nice to have a college here that you can actually go to.

02:20:46.700 --> 02:20:50.700
Can you think of anything else?

02:20:50.700 --> 02:20:54.700
I can't think of anything.

02:20:54.700 --> 02:20:57.700
It's been a very good interview.

02:20:57.700 --> 02:20:59.700
Thank you.

02:20:59.700 --> 02:21:00.700
Thank you.

02:21:00.700 --> 02:21:03.700
We appreciate you not supporting us.

02:21:03.700 --> 02:21:07.700
This has been a presentation of the Library of Congress

02:21:07.700 --> 02:21:13.700
and the Smithsonian National Museum of African American History and Culture.
